<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer14939710421455938938">Ian Frazier (b.1951) is an American writer and humorist. He is the author of <i>Travels in Siberia</i>, <i>Great Plains</i>, <i>On the Rez</i>, <i>Lamentations of the Father</i> and <i>Coyote V. Acme</i>, among other works, all published by Farrar, Straus and Giroux. He graduated from Harvard University. A frequent contributor to <i>The New Yorker</i>, he lives in Montclair, New Jersey.<br/><br/><a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://us.macmillan.com/author/ianfrazier'>http://us.macmillan.com/author/ianfra...</a></span>
  <span id="freeText14939710421455938938" style="display:none">Ian Frazier (b.1951) is an American writer and humorist. He is the author of <i>Travels in Siberia</i>, <i>Great Plains</i>, <i>On the Rez</i>, <i>Lamentations of the Father</i> and <i>Coyote V. Acme</i>, among other works, all published by Farrar, Straus and Giroux. He graduated from Harvard University. A frequent contributor to <i>The New Yorker</i>, he lives in Montclair, New Jersey.<br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://us.macmillan.com/author/ianfrazier">http://us.macmillan.com/author/ianfra...</a></span>
